calculateMinAmount(uint256,uint256,uint2.details: Calculates the minimum amount of tokens that should be received for the specified  amount with the given mid-price and maximum slippage.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be exchanged.
params.maxSlippage: The maximum slippage percentage as a fraction of the mid-price.
params.midPriceDenominator: The denominator of the mid-price for the token pair.
params.midPriceNumerator: The numerator of the mid-price for the token pair.

calculateMinAmount(uint256,uint256,uint2.return: The minimum amount of tokens that should be received as a uint256 value.

params.test: Set to true to skip implementation initialisation.

params.token: The address of the token to query.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.router: Address of the router to remove.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newMininumReports: The new update minimum number of reports required.

params.registryAddress: The address of a registry contract for routing to other contracts.

params.token: Address of the token to set.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to transfer.
params.to: The address of the recipient to transfer the tokens to.
params.token: The address of the token to transfer.
